('92cb730c-8b4f-46ef-9925-4fab953694c6', '4bafdd1a-a9ff-4c9f-ba1e-8c977fd00161', 'f6e940f7-75fd-4aaf-9790-e183174c2abd', '"when i was a child i would buy books via “book-orders” which involved checking off books to purchase from a catalog and mailing money. i was so excited to read books. as i got older, reading became associated more with homework than it was for pleasure. i re-kindled my enjoyment for reading during the summer after my first year of ucla. i was considering pursuing a career in mathematical finance. at the recommendation of my professor and good friend i picked up “my life as a quant.” the book was very well written and gave me the context to understand being a quant was not right for me. i was so thankful i picked up this book — it saved me from wasting time. i thought to myself — what else could i learn from reading? and so my reading journey began again. from 2010 onwards i would keep track of my favorite books. this year in particular was mostly focused on finance!"', 'c9eb7a01dd375cbdcd6669666ff36d37', 't', 'f', 'f', 'f', 'f', '1708623782646'),
