('92cb730c-8b4f-46ef-9925-4fab953694c6', '2f413d8f-b146-43a2-bf44-787e1efadb02', '275e5c3c-d565-4f5a-b832-4290cc6de915', '"the tao is the way of man''s cooperation with the natural course of the natural world, its principles can be found in the flow patterns of water. alan watts captures the spirit of the tao, the actual experience of that attitude to life. the ancient and timeless chinese wisdom is medicine for the ills of the west but it cannot be taken as medicine but intellectually swallowed to joyously infuse our being, transforming our individual lives and through them our society. drawing on ancient and modern sources, watts treats the chinese philosophy of tao in much the same way as he did zen buddhism in his classic the way of zen. alan watts has been described as the best guide to the spirit of the tao for a western readership. including an introduction to the chinese culture that is the foundation of the tao this is one of alan watts'' best-loved works."', 'b08126949d53ce097dd38988f1dec640', 't', 'f', 'f', 'f', 'f', '1708623782646'),
