('92cb730c-8b4f-46ef-9925-4fab953694c6', '0f7d30dc-500e-448f-9853-548a45da7d2d', 'f6e940f7-75fd-4aaf-9790-e183174c2abd', '"these are the books i recommend the most to others.\n\n\"unbearable lightness of being\" and \"on the road\" (the original scroll version)  are the most unique books i''ve read. most books i''ve read follow a certain archetype, these two really break the mold and expanded my views on how to write prose.\n\n\"east of eden\" is steinbeck''s magnum opus. the book is a masterclass in storytelling and weaving parallel narratives. if you enjoy seeing multiple storylines and themes come together, this is for you.\n\n\"the story of philosophy\" is my favorite philosophy book to date. probably one of the best resources for an introduction and overview of western philosophy. i love how the author includes historical context and criticism with each philosopher''s ideas. this enables you to critically evaluate and see the evolution of western thinking.\n\n\"how to win friends and influence people\" and \"the seven habits of highly effective people\" are often labeled \"self-help\" books but in my opinion they are more than that. not only do they speak to becoming self-confident and independent -- they elucidate the importance and path to interdependence. without a doubt, they have had the strongest impact on me in the last 20 years. if you were to only read two of my recommended books, it should be these."', '97297e75d03b50b0ae2a9a84a8eb3c21', 't', 'f', 'f', 'f', 'f', '1708623782646'),
